till%2C%20they%20didn't%20taste%20bad%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cap%20has%20handy%20(in%20theory)%20measurement%20markings%20for%20%C2%BE%20oz.%2C%201%20oz.%2C%20and%201.5%20oz.%20I%20would've%20found%20it%20even%20more%20useful%20if%20it%20had%20a%20%C2%BD%20oz.%20marking%2C%20which%20is%20also%20common%20in%20recipes.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%201.5%20oz.%20mark%20sits%20too%20closely%20to%20the%20top%20edge%20of%20the%20conical%20cap%2C%20meaning%20you%20have%20to%20be%20extra%20careful%20and%20slow%20as%20you%20pour%20ingredients%20in%20or%20they%20risk%20spilling%20out.%20Lastly%2C%20if%20you%20do%20choose%20to%20use%20the%20cap%20as%20a%20jigger%2C%20it%20could%20make%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20shaker%20slightly%20sticky%20once%20you%20flip%20it%20over%20and%20reattach%20it%20as%20a%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20for%20beginners%3A%20Crafthouse%20by%20Fortessa%20Boston%20Shaker%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20charles%20joly%20crafthouse%20fortessa%20shaker%20and%20strainer%20set%20on%20a%20table%20with%20a%20daiquiri.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6086fefd3f0560001881c0fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E17.5%20ounces%20(small%20tin)%20and%2024.25%20ounces%20(large%20tin)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E18%2F8%C2%A0stainless%20steel%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20included%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETwo%20tins%2C%20one%20Hawthorne%20strainer%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDishwasher-safe%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDesigned%20by%20an%20expert%2C%20doesn't%20leak%2C%20frosts%20up%20quickly%2C%20sturdy%20construction%2C%20includes%20strainer%C2