xcellent%3A%20the%20coils%20fit%20inside%20and%20the%20wings%20fit%20over%20the%20large%20tin%20comfortably%2C%20and%20all%20the%20tiny%20holes%20strained%20the%20contents%20completely.%20You%20can%20complete%20the%20set%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_113017_best-cocktail-shakers-20%26h%3De1b0454be21768e2c28c2733fe038222e092723d215fc8d2dd68a2553572ea01%26postID%3D61b8efc6f2a36b1ac9f41771%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fbest-cocktail-shaker%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.surlatable.com%252Fcrafthouse-by-fortessa-jigger%252FPRO-4569547.html%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejigger%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20two-sided%20and%20has%20all%20the%20appropriate%20and%20common%20measurements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20stainless%20steel%20cocktail%20shaker%20is%20the%20best%20tried%20and%20true%20option.%20Stainless%20steel%20is%20durable%20and%20lightweight%2C%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20drinks%20very%20cold%20very%20quickly%20when%20used%20with%20ice.%20This%20material%20is%20easy%20to%20clean%20and%20dishwasher-safe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Cocktail%20shakers%20range%20in%20size%20and%20typically%20hold%20between%2018%20and%2028%20ounces.%20Consider%20how%20often%20you're%20making%20cocktails%20for%20a%20big%20crowd.%20If%20you%20regularly%20host%20cocktail%20parties%20with%20friends%2C%20a%20roomy%20shaker%20might%20be%20best.%20If%20you%20usually%20just%20have%20cocktails%20for%20two%2C%20a%20smaller%20size%20will%20take%20up%20less%20room%20in%20your%20cabinets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncluded%20accessories%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20need%20a%20shaker%2C%20jigger%2C%20and%20strainer%20to%20make%20cocktails.%20Do%20you%20already%20own%20the%20jigger%20and%20strainer%2C%20or%20do%20you%20need%20all%20three%20in%20one%20set%3F%20It%20can%20be%20more%20convenient%20to%20buy%20a%20shaker%20with%20a%20built-in%20jigger%20lid%20and%20strainer.%20Shaking%20tins%20typically%20don't%20come%20with%20the%20extra%20accessories%2C%20so%20keep%20them%20in%20mind%20when%20shopping.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeal%20strength%20and%20durability%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nothing's%20worse%20than%20shaking%20up%20your%20cocktail%20and%20spilling%20half%20the%20drink%20in%20the%20process.%20A%20good%20seal%20is%20essential%20to%20make%20sure%20you're%20not%20losing%20your%20liquor%20as%20you%20mix%20up%20the%20ingredients.%20When%20shopping%20for%20a%20cocktail%20shaker%2C%20pay%20attention%20to%20reviews%20that%20discuss%20the%20seal%20strength%20and%20how%20well%20two%20parts%20of%20the%20tin%20fit%20together%20%E2%80%94%20a%20just-right%20fit%20means%20a%20solid%20seal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20tested%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bowl%20of%20juice%20surrounded%20by%20lemons%20limes%20eggs%20blood%20orange%20mixer%20rum%20and%20whiskey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6086ffa63f0560001881c106%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20cocktail%2C%20we%20noted%20and%20compared%20the%20following%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaste%2C%20consistency%2C%20and%20smoothness%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Whether%20the%20ingredients%20were%20incorporated%20evenly%20and%20if%20the%20cocktail%20tasted%20balanced.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETemperature%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHow%20cold%20the%20cocktail%20was%20after%20shaking.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EVolume%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20final%20volume%20after%20shaking%2C%20to%20see%20the%20effect%20of%20the%20shaker%20on%20ice%20melt%20and%20dilution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20example%20of%20our%20test%20results%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20border%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EProduct%20name%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EDaiquiri%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EWhiskey%20Sour%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EOXO%20Steel%20Cocktail%20Shaker%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECold%2C%20didn't%20seem%20to%20mix%20all%20the%20ingredients%20super%20evenly%20-%20some%20sips%20were%20very%20rum-y%20while%20others%20were%20more%20citrusy%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemperature%3A%2034%C2%B0F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVolume%3A%20%E2%85%9D%20cup%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReally%20thick%20(too%20thick)%20and%20even%20foam%2C%20smooth%2C%20cold%2C%20again%20didn't%20seem%20to%20mix%20all%20ingredients%20super%20evenly%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemperature%3A%2034%C2%B0F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVolume%3A%201%20cup%20(lot%20of%20dilution%3F)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20%3Cstrong%3Eseal%20strength%20and%20overall%20durability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20of%20the%20best%20cocktail%20shakers%2C%20we%20filled%20each%20shaker%20with%205%20oz.%20water%20and%20%C2%BD%20cup%20of%20ice%2C%20created%20a%20tight%20seal%20or%20closed%20the%20lid%20(depending%20on%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20Boston%20or%20cobbler%20shaker)%2C%20and%20dropped%20it%20on%20concrete%20ground%20from%20shoulder%20height%20three%20times.%20We%20noted%20if%20the%20seal%20broke%2C%20scratches%20and%20dings%20to%20the%20shaker%2C%20and%20other%20durability%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20%3Cstrong%3Eease%20of%20use%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20we%20noted%20the%20size%2C%20weight%2C%20feel%2C%20comfort%2C%20and%20any%20leakage%20of%20each%20shaker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaiquiri%20recipe%20used%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2%20ounces%20light%20rum%20(Bacardi)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1%20ounce%20lime%20juice%20(fresh-squeezed)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%BE%20ounces%20simple%20syrup%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%BD%20cup%20ice%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlood%20orange%20whiskey%20sour%20recipe%20used%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2%20ounces%20whiskey%20(Kikori)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1.5%20ounces%20blood%20orange%20juice%20(Stirrings)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E0.5%20ounces%20lemon%20juice%20(fresh-squeezed)%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1%20ounce%20simple%20syrup%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1%20egg%20white%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%BD%20cup%20ice%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECocktail%20shaker%20and%20home%20bartending%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20graphic%20comparing%20the%20features%20of%20a%20Cobbler%20shaker%20and%20Boston%20shaker.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F608701880da8f4001803380e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Powell%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20do%20you%20need%20a%20cocktail%20shaker%20in%20the%20first%20place%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20general%20rule%20of%20thumb%2C%20cocktails%20that%20contain%20only%20spirits%20are%20stirred%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Charles%20Joly%2C%20a%20Diageo%20World%20Class%20bartending%20champion%2C%20official%20bartender%20for%20the%20Oscars%20and%20Emmys%2C%20and%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrafthousecocktails.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrafthouse%20Cocktails%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BStirring%20chills%2C%20dilutes%2C%20combines%20ingredients%2C%20and%20adds%20texture%2C%20but%20that%20last%20point%20is%20the%20big%20difference.%20Stirring%20doesn't%20aerate%20the%20cocktail%20like%20shaking%20does.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStir%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECocktails%20containing%20only%20spirits%2C%20like%20a%20Negroni%2C%20Manhattan%2C%20or%20martini%20(%26quot%3BYes%2C%20James%20Bond%20was%20wrong%2C%20you%20do%20not%20shake%20a%20martini%2C%26quot%3B%20emphasized%20Ivy%20Mix%2C%20partner%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiascobk.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFIASCO!%20Wine%20and%20Spirits%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20head%20bartender%20and%20co-owner%20of%20cocktail%20bar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleyendabk.com%2F%5C%22%3ELeyenda%3C%2Fa%3E).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShake%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECocktails%20containing%20citrus%2C%20egg%20white%2C%20and%20other%20non-alcoholic%20ingredients%2C%20like%20a%20daiquiri%2C%20whiskey%20sour%2C%20or%20Cosmopolitan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20a%20Boston%20shaker%20and%20a%20cobbler%20shaker%3F%20Which%20one%20is%20better%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Boston%20shaker%20has%20two%20parts%20%E2%80%94%20two%20tins%20that%20you%20push%20together%20to%20create%20a%20natural%20seal.%20The%20measuring%20jigger%20and%20strainer%20are%20distinct%20parts%20and%20may%20be%20sold%20separately%20or%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20Boston%20shaker%20set.%20A%20cobbler%20shaker%20has%20three%20parts%20%E2%80%94%20one%20large%20tin%2C%20a%20much%20smaller%20top%20piece%20that%20is%20screwed%20on%20or%20placed%20on%20top%20and%20contains%20a%20built-in%20strainer%2C%20and%20a%20cap.%20Sometimes%20the%20cap%20or%20smaller%20top%20piece%20has%20interior%20measurement%20markings%20so%20it%20can%20double%20as%20a%20jigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFunctionally%2C%20cobbler%20shakers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20leak%20and%20they're%20smaller%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20to%20shake%20and%20%26quot%3Bwhip%20in%20sufficient%20amounts%20of%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Chetiyawardana.%20But%20because%20they%20have%20a%20built-in%20strainer%20and%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20create%20a%20natural%20seal%2C%20they%20may%20be%20more%20approachable%20and%20convenient%20to%20use%20for%20some%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoston%20shakers%20could%20have%20a%20learning%20curve%20because%20you%20must%20place%20one%20tin%20in%20the%20other%20at%20the%20correct%20angle%20in%20order%20to%20create%20a%20tight%20seal.%20However%2C%20well-designed%20and%20sized%20Boston%20shaker%20tins%20should%20fit%20perfectly%20in%20each%20other%20and%20are%20also%20easy%20to%20release.%20They're%20also%20really%20durable%2C%20and%20in%20our%20durability%20tests%2C%20they%20suffered%20the%20least%20damage.%20When%20dropped%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20they%20hold%20all%20the%20contents%20in.%20Even%20if%20you%20have%20a%20too-vigorous%20shaking%20session%20and%20the%20shaker%20slips%20from%20your%20hands%2C%20your%20cocktail%20will%20still%20be%20safe.%20Like%20most%20professional%20bartenders%2C%20we%20prefer%20the%20Boston%20shaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EHow%20do%20you%20shake%20a%20cocktail%20shaker%3F%20How%20long%20do%20you%20shake%20it%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20vigorous.%20%26quot%3BThe%20key%20is%20you%20want%20to%20shake%20it%20awake%2C%20not%20rock%20it%20to%20sleep...I%20recommend%20channeling%20your%20inner%20quarterback%20and%20really%20getting%20some%20movement%20in%20there%2C%20being%20sure%20to%20put%20a%20hand%20on%20the%20top%20and%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20shaker%20so%20nothing%20explodes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mix.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20recommended%20anywhere%20from%2010%20to%2020%20seconds%20and%20explained%20that%20the%20exact%20duration%20can%20depend%20on%20the%20ingredients%2C%20amount%20of%20ice%2C%20and%20specific%20cocktail.%20The%20biggest%20thing%20to%20remember%20is%20that%20you%20need%20to%20shake%20until%20the%20outside%20frosts%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20Boston%20shaker%2C%20insert%20the%20small%20tin%20into%20the%20larger%20tin%20at%20an%20angle%20so%20that%20you%20create%20a%20flat%20line%20on%20one%20side.%20Apply%20some%20pressure%20to%20seal%2C%20and%20hold%20the%20shaker%20with%20two%20hands.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20to%20keep%20my%20pointer%20and%20index%20finger%20on%20the%20top%20of%20the%20outside%20tin%20and%20my%20thumb%20over%20the%20top%20of%20the%20tin%20closest%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20brands%20do%20bartenders%20like%20and%20use%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCocktail%20Kingdom%20is%20tried%20and%20true%20and%20I%20also%20love%20Charles%20Joly's%20Fortessa%20Shaker%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mix.%C2%A0%20Holborough%20also%20cited%20Cocktail%20Kingdom%2C%20while%20Joly%20recommended%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsantokunyc.com%2Fproducts%2Fcopy-of-birdy-cocktail-shaker-500ml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEric%20Lorinz'%20Birdy%20shaker%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Chetiyawardana%20favors%20Japanese%20and%20German%20brands%20in%20general%20to%20find%20the%20best%20cocktail%20shaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3ESome%20final%20tips%20and%20tricks%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20using%20a%20Boston%20shaker%2C%20shake%20with%20the%20small%20tin%20facing%20you.%20In%20case%20of%20any%20leakage%2C%20the%20liquid%20will%20land%20on%20you%20instead%20of%20your%20audience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20make%20a%20cocktail%20but%20don't%20have%20the%20best%20cocktail%20shaker%20on%20hand%2C%20you%20can%20always%20use%20Tupperware%20or%20a%20jam%20jar%2C%20said%20Chetiyawardana.%20%26quot%3BA%20shaker%20simply%20gives%20you%20comfort%20and%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECocktail%20shakers%20glossary%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20overhead%20shot%20of%20measuring%20cups%20jiggers%20and%20strainers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F608701df0da8f40018033810%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDry%20shake%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShaking%20cocktail%20ingredients%20together%20without%20ice%2C%20typically%20done%20for%20cocktails%20containing%20egg%20white%20or%20cream.%20The%20higher%20temperature%20lets%20the%20ingredients%20mix%20together%20better%20and%20create%20more%20aeration%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20thicker%20foam.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWet%20shake%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShaking%20cocktail%20ingredients%20together%20with%20ice%2C%20which%20help%20dilute%20and%20chill%20the%20drink.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJigger%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20small%2C%20usually%20two-sided%20measuring%20cup%20that%20you%20use%20to%20measure%20and%20pour%20liquid%20ingredients.%20The%20standard%20size%20is%201.5%20ounces%20on%20one%20side%20and%200.75%20ounces%20on%20the%20other.%20There%20may%20be%20additional%2C%20smaller%20markings%20inside.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHawthorne%20strainer%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20common%20type%20of%20strainer%20that%20is%20flat%20and%20has%20small%20holes%2C%20a%20spring%20on%20one%20side%2C%20a%20finger%20tab%20or%20indentation%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20and%20sometimes%20side%20wings.%20It's%20placed%20spring%20side%20down%20over%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20shaker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuddler%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20tool%20used%20to%20mash%20fruits%2C%20herbs%2C%20or%20spices%20to%20bring%20out%20their%20flavors.%20Drinks%20like%20mojitos%20and%20mint%20juleps%20require%20muddling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E18%2F8%20stainless%20steel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20type%20of%20stainless%20steel%20that%20is%20made%20up%20of%2018%25%20chromium%20and%208%25%20nickel.%20It's%20extremely%20resistant%20to%20corrosion%20and%20commonly%20used%20in%20commercial%20food%20processing%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-c